stream: then shall ye suck, ye shall be borne upon \add her\add*
sides, and be dandled upon \add her\add* knees. 
\v 13  As one whom his mother comforteth, so will I comfort you; and ye shall be
comforted in Jerusalem. 
\v 14  And when ye see \add this\add*, your heart shall rejoice,
and your bones shall flourish like an herb: and the hand of the \nd LORD\nd*
shall be known toward his servants, and \add his\add* indignation
toward his enemies. 
\p
\v 15  For, behold, the \nd LORD\nd* will come with fire, and with his
chariots like a whirlwind, to render his anger with fury, and his
rebuke with flames of fire. 
\v 16  For by fire and by his sword will the \nd LORD\nd* plead with all
flesh: and the slain of the \nd LORD\nd* shall be many. 
\v 17  They that sanctify themselves, and purify themselves in the
gardens behind one \add tree\add* in the midst, eating  swine’s flesh,
and the abomination, and the mouse, shall be consumed together, saith
the \nd LORD\nd*.\f + \fr 66.17  \ft behind…: or, one after another\f*
\v 18 For I \add know\add* their works and their thoughts: it shall
come, that I will gather all nations and tongues; and they shall
come, and see my glory. 
\v 19  And I will set a sign among them, and I will send those that
escape of them unto the nations, \add to\add* Tarshish, Pul, and
Lud, that draw the bow, \add to\add* Tubal, and Javan, \add to\add*
the isles afar off, that have not heard my fame, neither have seen
my glory; and they shall declare my glory among the Gentiles. 
\v 20  And they shall bring all your brethren \add for\add* an offering
unto the \nd LORD\nd* out of all nations upon horses, and in chariots,
and in litters, and upon mules, and upon swift beasts, to my holy
